metadata.name: aprendizajes #109
metadata.description:
aprendizajes is a generative art project that pays a tribute to the process of learning. 25% of primary proceeds go to Save The Children. Full description of the artwork+instructions here: https://www.iillucid.com/aprendizajes/

The artwork allows the user to:

* Change resolution: press 'd' followed by any number from 1 to 9 to add that amount to the pixel density. If you get a black screen you have surpassed what your graphics card can handle: press d + 0 to reset the pixel density. You can fine tune pressing d followed by + or - (+/- 0.5).
* Save image: press 's' to save the current image as png. For a higher resolution png, 1st increase the resolution using 'd' and then save the image with 's'.
* Tune image parameters: press 'z' (brightness), 'x' (contrast), 'g' (gamma), 'b' (blur) followed by + or - to adjust. Toggle tuning with 'a'. Press 'n' then + or - to adjust amount of noise.
* Redraw: 'r' (changes how lines are drawn)

It is recommended to read the full instructions on the article.

metadata.name: Geode #44
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - “slow=1”: Draw only one shape per frame.

metadata.name: Geometric colorful shapes 3 #6
metadata.description:
This art tool uses an algorithmic approach that includes genetic and selection processes to generate unique and colorful abstract shapes. With the ability to adjust various parameters, each design is truly one-of-a-kind, and you can easily save and share your creations using our unique hash function. So go ahead, get creative, and let the program surprise you with its endless possibilities! Remember, the program is the only creator of these colorful shapes, thanks to its algorithmic approach, and if you like the result, you can support my previous projects.
The program has a default resolution of 1500x1500.

metadata.name: Sands of Time #48
metadata.description:
+ 50% of proceeds will be donated to Cure Parkinson's
+ Minters get 4.5% of royalties from secondary sales
+ Press 1 to 8 to change the resolution of the render (1: lowest resolution, 8: highest resolution)

----

STATEMENT

The sands of time rise up,
Their scapes so bold and old,
In their dance with the winds,
As light and shadow dance and play,
In this land of endless day.
A sight of quiet grace,
On a canvas of the desert's face.
A song of resilience,
In a world that changes by the hour.

"Sands of Time" is a rhetoric of transience and impermanence inspired by the dunes. It is a comtemplation of the passing of time, the inevitability of change, and the beauty that can be found in impermanence. It is an invitation to reflect on the fluidity of life and our own place within the grander scheme of things. A testament to the resilience and grit required to survive in a constantly changing world. Despite the harsh conditions and ever-present threat of change, the desert sands endure, shifting but not breaking; their beauty and strength undiminished.

Made of several overlapping curved lines, each piece is a depiction of movement and fluidity, symbolizing sands in a constant state of motion. The curves blend and mix, creating new patterns and hues where they overlap, much like the way that life experiences blend and mix to create new and unique outcomes. The uneven distribution of grains across each piece represents timelessness. Areas of low accumulation of grains are a reminder of the years of constant erosion. The sands of time have existed and will exist in a state of constant motion and change for eons, for the lifetime. This way, each piece also evokes nostalgia, as we ponder on our past lives.

“It’s your reaction to adversity, not adversity itself that determines how your life’s story will develop.” ― Dieter F. Uchtdorf

metadata.name: Blooming dancers #86
metadata.description:
Inspired by the similarity between a dancer's dress and a blooming flower.

It's an homage to art and nature, with exclusive features including :

- A choice between 12 modern and 12 rarer Artist inspired color palettes (Thanks to http://www.colorlisa.com/)
- 1 to 5 dancers
- Various Soft and Hard framing options
- A unique full canvas system which allows the collector to display on portrait, landscape or square screen the art
- A lot of line and background style variations.

The art is better viewed in full screen, captures don't display the fine details

patxol - 2022

Made with p5js

metadata.name: PEGS #345
metadata.description: Taking inspiration from work by Karl Gerstner, Armin Hofmann, Nick Kuder and Dmitri Cherniak, PEGS explores the limits of constrained algorithmic variation. Based on the simple, playful idea of wrapping a string across a board of pegs, it shows how endless possibilities can be achieved with just a basic set of rules and a few primary colors. When done right, generative art challenges us to answer fundamental questions around creativity, beauty, and life itself.

metadata.name: Unsquare composition #49
metadata.description:
Inspired by Jazz, Unsquare composition I experiments with the notion of non-squared rhythmic forms, where freedom and improvisation take as a premise the idea of an imperfection where we can also find harmony. 

Please do not expect perfect results.

unknowable 2022
